A **prospective cohort study** is ideal here because it allows comparison of fat content between pre-term and term infants *before* any outcomes occur, ensuring temporal clarity and minimizing recall bias. This design efficiently captures the exposure (pre-term vs. term) and outcome (milk fat content) in real time. Other options (case-control, longitudinal, ambispective) are less suited for this comparative, exposure-based question.
